df<-df[index,]
for (i in c(1:3,11:12)){   #turn character variables into factor variables
  df[,i] <- as.factor(df[,i])
}

#The Bar chart #for a categorical/discrete variable

ggplot(df, aes(manufacturer))+
  geom_bar(width = 0.5)

ggplot(df, aes(manufacturer))+
  geom_bar(width = 0.5) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6)) 

ggplot(df, aes(manufacturer))+
  geom_bar(aes(fill=fuel_type), width = 0.5) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65))

ggplot(df, aes(manufacturer))+
  geom_bar(aes(fill=fuel_type), width = 0.5) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6)) +
  labs(title="Categorywise Bar Chart", 
       subtitle="Manufacturer of vehicles")

ggplot(df, aes(manufacturer))+
  geom_bar(aes(fill=fuel_type), width = 0.5) +
  coord_flip()+
  labs(title="Categorywise Bar Chart", 
       subtitle="Manufacturer of vehicles")

#The histogram #for a continuous variable

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price)) + 
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price)) + 
  geom_histogram(bins=5)

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price)) + 
  geom_histogram(bins=15, color='blue', fill='green')

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),bins=15, color='blue', fill='green')+
  geom_density(alpha=.2, fill='black')

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price, color=fuel_type)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),bins=15, color='blue', fill='green')+
  geom_density(alpha=.2, fill='black')+
  theme(legend.position="top")

ggplot(df, aes(x=buy_price)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),bins=15, color='blue', fill='green')+
  geom_density(alpha=.2, fill='black')+
  facet_grid(~fuel_type)

#The Scatter plot #x nad y are both continuous (numerical) variables

ggplot(df, aes(x=mileage, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point()

ggplot(df, aes(x=mileage, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point() +
  labs(y="Horsepower", 
       x="Mileage", 
       title="Scatterplot")

ggplot(df, aes(x=mileage, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  xlim(c(0, 250000)) + 
  ylim(c(0, 150)) + 
  labs(y="Horsepower", 
       x="Mileage", 
       title="Scatterplot")
## Warning: Removed 174 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

ggplot(df, aes(x=mileage, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point(aes(col=fuel_type, shape=fuel_type)) + 
  labs(y="Horsepower", 
       x="Mileage", 
       title="Scatterplot")

ggplot(df, aes(x=kw, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point() +
  labs(y="Kw", 
       x="Horsepower", 
       title="Scatterplot")

ggplot(df, aes(x=kw, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="lm", se=F) +
  labs(y="Kw", 
       x="Horsepower", 
       title="Scatterplot")

ggplot(df, aes(x=kw, y=horsepower)) + 
  geom_count(col="tomato3", show.legend=T)+ #to avoid overlapping
  labs(y="Kw", 
       x="Horsepower", 
       title="Scatterplot")

#The Boxplot #x - categorical variable and y - continuous variable

ggplot(df, aes(x = sourcing_country, y = built_year))+
  geom_boxplot()

ggplot(df, aes(x = sourcing_country, y = built_year))+
  geom_boxplot(fill="plum")

ggplot(df, aes(x = sourcing_country, y = built_year))+
  geom_boxplot(fill="plum")+
  labs(y = "Years", x = "Country", title="Country per years")

ggplot(df, aes(x = sourcing_country, y = built_year))+
  geom_boxplot(fill="plum")+
  labs(y = "Years", x = "Country", title="Country per years")+
  theme_classic()

ggplot(df, aes(x = fuel_type, y = buy_price))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=fuel_type))+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6)) + 
  labs(y = "Price", x = "Fuel", title="Fuel vs Price")+
  theme_classic()

ggplot(df, aes(x = fuel_type, y = buy_price))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(fill=fuel_type))+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6)) + 
  labs(y = "Price", x = "Fuel", title="Fuel vs Price")+
  theme_classic()+
  scale_x_discrete(limits=c("Benzin"))
## Warning: Removed 293 rows containing missing values (stat_boxplot).

ggplot(df, aes(x = manufacturer, y = built_year))+
  geom_boxplot(aes(col=manufacturer))+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=65, vjust=0.6)) + 
  labs(y = "Years", x = "Manufacturer", title="Manufacturer per years")+
  coord_flip()  #horizontal display

#The Tufte boxplot # - for minimization

ggplot(df, aes(x = fuel_type, y = buy_price))+
  geom_tufteboxplot()+
  labs(y = "Price", x = "Fuel", subtitle="Fuel vs Price", title="Tufte Styled Boxplot")

#The x and y are discrete

ggplot(df, aes(fuel_type, sourcing_country)) +
  geom_jitter(aes(color = fuel_type), size = 1)
